Asia
--
Pakistan
- Sindh (Karachi). 4 Apr 2018. As many as 10 more dengue fever cases were detected across Karachi in a week, taking the reported toll of cases to 216 in the city since 1 Jan 2018.
According to the weekly report issued by Prevention and Control Program for Dengue in Sindh, at least 10 new dengue fever cases surfaced across the city in a week. No case was reported from other parts of the province.
A total of 229 dengue cases have been reported throughout Sindh, including 216 in Karachi and 13 in the rest of the province.
http://www.thesundaily.my/news/2018/04/06/10-dengue-deaths-sabah-until-march
- Sindh (Karachi). 10 Apr 2018.Cases rise to 235 since 1 Jan 2018 with 19 new cases in Karachi and 2 new cases in Sindh Province. Karachi reports one death.
https://www.brecorder.com/2018/04/09/410609/a19-more-dengue-cases-reported-in-karachi/

India
- Karanataka. 10 Apr 2018. 305 cases in Bengaluru. In Karnataka there have been 703 cases reported.
https://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/health-and-wellbeing/100418/305-dengue-cases-already-in-city-bengaluru-tops-list-in-stat.html
- Telangana. 7 Apr 2018. 400 suspected cases with 134 confirmed cases in all 31 districts. Hyderabad - 2 deaths in Mahboob colony, 154 suspected cases, 51 confirmed.
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/killer-sting-back-51-dengue-cases-in-just-45-days-in-hyderabad/articleshow/63653145.cms

Philippines
- National. 13 Apr 2018. 1967 Dengvaxia vaccinees hospitalized due to dengue in 2 years: DOH Sanofi says no-one has died.
http://news.abs-cbn.com/news/ 04/13/18/nearly-2000- dengvaxia-vaccinees- hospitalized-due-to-dengue-in- 2-years-doh
- Pangasinan. 10 Apr 2018. More than 182 percent rise in cases with 982 cases in the period 1 Jan - 2 Apr 2018. Urdaneta City recorded the highest number of dengue cases in the province with 119, followed by Binmaley (65), Mangaldan (55), Asingan (50), Sta. Barbara (48), San Carlos City (47), Lingayen (47), Bolinao (45), Binalonan (36) and Bayambang (32).
http://www.sunstar.com.ph/pangasinan/local-news/2018/04/10/dengue-cases-182-pangasinan-597713

Malaysia
- Petaling Jaya. 2 Apr 2018. Petaling Jaya City Council (MBPJ) recorded a 54% decline in dengue cases compared to the same time last year [2017]. Based on the council's statistics, 845 dengue cases were reported in 2017, in contrast to 387 cases this year [2018], said mayor Datuk Mohd Azizi Mohd Zain during MBPJ's full board meeting. He said the Search and Destroy Aedes Rangers (Sedar) teams have reduced the number of dengue cases.
http://www.thestar.com.my/metro/metro-news/2018/04/02/mbpj-fewer-dengue-cases-as-of-march-this-year/#IXIOWH907SOHQSxe.99
- Kunak. 8 Apr 2018. Some 113 cases, including 4 deaths, due to dengue fever have been recorded in Kunak within a period of 3 months until March this year [2018].
http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/113-dengue-cases-four-deaths-recorded-in-kunak
- Sabah. 7 Apr 2018. 958 cases with 10 deaths until 31 Mar [2018]
http://www.thesundaily.my/news/2018/04/06/10-dengue-deaths-sabah-until-march

La Reunion Island. 2 Apr 2018. 588 confirmed cases in the west, and south of the island, 154 confirmed
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/reunion-dengue-outbreak-continues-rise-588-indigenous-cases-year-12164/
La Reunion Island. 10 Apr 2018. 167 additional autochthonous dengue cases reported during the past week. Total rises to 755 cases; DEN-2 predominates. http://outbreaknewstoday.com/autochthonous-dengue-fever-reunion-59266/
La Reunion Island. 15 Apr 2018. Nearly 1000 confirmed cases in the north, west and south of the island since 1 Jan 2018.
A dengue epidemic is currently affecting western and southern Reunion. After an unusual circulation of the virus during the austral winter of 2017, the number of dengue cases has gradually increased since the beginning of 2018, with an intensification in February 2018. Public Health France publishes a "point of situation" report and provides reminders about preventive actions to adopt.
On 26 Mar 2018, the Prefect of Reunion declared the level to be a "low intensity epidemic" of the ORSEC arbovirus control device. The intervention unit in the Indian Ocean region provides epidemiological surveillance of dengue fever on Reunion Island and publishes its data every week in an epidemiological point. The current epidemic could continue to intensify in the coming weeks. Indeed, the population is not immune to dengue fever (only 3.1 percent of blood donors tested for dengue in 2008 had antibodies against the virus), and current weather conditions are conducive to vector development.

Epidemiological situation as of 9 Apr 2018:
- 992 indigenous cases reported since 1 Jan 2018
- 237 cases were confirmed during the last week, one case imported from Mauritius
- Prevalence of DENV-2 serotype
- A circulation area of the virus identified in the north
- Continuation of the epidemic in the west and south
http://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/Actualites/Epidemie-de-dengue-a-La-Reunion-pres-de-1-000-cas-confirmes-dans-le-nord-l-ouest-et-le-sud-de-l-ile-depuis-le-1er-janvier-2018

Pacific
------
- Tonga. 30 Mar 2018. Tonga has recorded 124 cases of dengue since the beginning of the year [2018].
https://www.radionz.co.nz/ international/pacific-news/ 353742/dengue-affecting-124- people-in-tonga-so-far-this- year

- Samoa. 9 Apr 2018. Serotype 2 Outbreak in Samoa, 2017/2018. The cumulative total as of 18 Mar 2018 is 3255, with a national attack rate of 16.6 per 1000 population. Dengue fever continues to spread geographically, mostly in the Apia Urban and North West Upolu regions. A majority of those affected are 5-9-year-old children, which make up 31 percent of the total cases. There have not been any dengue related deaths reported, hence the total dengue-related mortality remains at 5.
https://reliefweb.int/report/samoa/dengue-serotype-2-outbreak-samoa-20172018-sitrep-no-9-18th-march-2018

